### Job Advertisement
**Position:** Hi-Fi Prototype Designer&nbsp;&nbsp;
**Company:** Untap Group Pty Ltd&nbsp;&nbsp;
**Location:** [Location] / Remote&nbsp;&nbsp;
**Employment Type:** Contract / Full-time&nbsp;&nbsp;
#### About Us:&nbsp;&nbsp;
Untap is a cutting-edge technology company revolutionizing the recruitment industry through innovative IT solutions. We are dedicated to creating seamless and user-friendly experiences for both job seekers and employers.
#### Job Description:&nbsp;&nbsp;
We are seeking a talented and experienced Hi-Fi Prototype Designer to join our dynamic team. As a Hi-Fi Prototype Designer, you will be responsible for creating high-fidelity prototypes that showcase the user interface and experience of our recruitment IT application. You will work closely with our product development team to bring concepts to life and ensure that our application meets the needs of our users.
#### Responsibilities:&nbsp;&nbsp;
- Design and develop high-fidelity prototypes for our recruitment IT application.
- Collaborate with product managers and developers to iterate on designs and incorporate feedback.
- Ensure that the user interface is intuitive, visually appealing, and aligns with our brand guidelines.
- Conduct user testing to gather feedback and make improvements to the prototypes.
- Stay up-to-date with industry trends and best practices in UI/UX design.
#### Requirements:&nbsp;&nbsp;
- Proven experience as a Hi-Fi Prototype Designer or similar role.
- Proficiency in design tools such as Adobe XD, Sketch, or Figma.
- Strong portfolio showcasing your previous design work and projects.
- Excellent communication and collaboration skills.
- Understanding of user-centered design principles.
- Bachelor&#039;s degree in Design, Human-Computer Interaction, or related field (preferred).
We haven&rsquo;t set an open hourly rate we want you to pitch your price. Person will be chosen on merits and not necessarily on who is the cheapest.
Join us in revolutionizing the recruitment industry with cutting-edge technology and user-centric design!<b>Skills</b>:        Mobile UI Design,                     Software Design,                     Functional Prototype,                     Mobile App Design,                     Product Design,                     Wireframing,                     Prototyping,                     Graphic Design,                     Adobe Photoshop,                     InVision
